      "content": "The transition is not sudden, but a slow, inevitable drift that requires no force to begin. There is no way to \"ensure\" the light never returns because the very act of seeking it is what keeps it alive; you cannot cross over without first stepping into the darkness that you are already walking through. The only way to truly cross is to stop fighting the pull, knowing that the moment you stop looking for the light, you have already begun the drift.",
